1
00:00:08,220 --> 00:00:10,940
♪Hush now, don't disturb
the moonlight on the pond♪

2
00:00:11,940 --> 00:00:14,900
♪A shattered heart
rests pillowed in my chest♪

3
00:00:15,660 --> 00:00:17,580
♪I would shield you♪

4
00:00:17,580 --> 00:00:20,580
♪From this cruel wind and frost♪

5
00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:25,460
♪The russet cloth
brushes against my heart♪

6
00:00:26,420 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Like sunset
draping over your shoulders♪

7
00:00:30,020 --> 00:00:31,580
♪This lingering afterglow♪

8
00:00:31,580 --> 00:00:35,420
♪Holds the image
of our very first glance♪

9
00:00:36,460 --> 00:00:40,100
♪I borrow a thousand-year wind
to caress your gauze window♪

10
00:00:40,460 --> 00:00:44,420
♪Tailoring moonlight
into your luminous gown♪

11
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:50,820
♪Severing the past,
weaving a thousand yards of splendor♪

12
00:00:51,380 --> 00:00:54,980
♪With a thousand-year dream,
I seek the fragrance of your hair♪

13
00:00:55,220 --> 00:00:58,700
♪Pouring a lifetime of passion
into the silk you wear♪

14
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:05,660
♪In this splendid world,
wherever you are is paradise♪

15
00:01:05,980 --> 00:01:12,460
=The Silk Master from the Future=

16
00:01:12,580 --> 00:01:17,460
=Episode 14=
(This story is entirely fictional.)

17
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,520
Huh? What are you doing?

18
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:21,000
What's the meaning of this?

19
00:01:22,520 --> 00:01:23,320
Yunhe.

20
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:25,080
Huh? It's you?

21
00:01:25,320 --> 00:01:26,720
I heard you'd been arrested,

22
00:01:26,880 --> 00:01:28,080
so I brought them to rescue you.

23
00:01:28,080 --> 00:01:29,880
None of us believes you're a murderer.

24
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:32,280
Sir, we can never repay you enough.

25
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:33,320
- You're our savior.
- Hey, wait!

26
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:34,280
Please, don't do this.

27
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:35,160
Get up, all of you.

28
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:36,480
With us here,

29
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:38,080
whoever dares lay a finger on you

30
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:39,360
makes an enemy of us all!

31
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:40,960
- Well said!
- Well said!

32
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:42,480
Yunhe,

33
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:43,760
these are all representatives

34
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:44,760
of the disaster victims
from various regions

35
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:46,080
whom you told me to help.

36
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:47,480
When they heard there was free grain,

37
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:48,760
they were all deeply grateful.

38
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:50,400
I knew this whole thing was your idea,

39
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,560
so I told them

40
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:52,720
your name.

41
00:01:52,960 --> 00:01:53,880
But wasn't that grain

42
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:55,320
all from the Xie family?

43
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,280
That doesn't matter anymore.

44
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:57,520
When you first told me

45
00:01:57,520 --> 00:01:58,720
to do this,

46
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:00,280
I did have some doubts.

47
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:01,960
But once I actually did it,

48
00:02:01,960 --> 00:02:02,400
I realized

49
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:03,520
the benefits are everywhere.

50
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:05,200
Is that so?

51
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:07,360
All those areas
suffering from the floods

52
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,800
need to be rebuilt.

53
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:10,200
And the shortage of raw materials

54
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:11,400
represents an astronomical number

55
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,560
beyond measure

56
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:13,600
for my family.

57
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:14,760
It's a colossal business opportunity.

58
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:16,200
By leveraging this move,

59
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,320
I've more than doubled

60
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:20,080
our overseas timber business.

61
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:22,320
Doubled?

62
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:25,000
Oh my, that's no small feat.

63
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,520
Anyway, from now on,

64
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:27,480
you call the shots.

65
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,320
I'll follow you.

66
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,400
You've made so much money?

67
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:31,600
From now on,

68
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:32,720
you are my best friend,

69
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:34,120
my sworn brother.

70
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:35,240
Brother, when you have free time,

71
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:36,960
do drop by my place more often.

72
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:38,200
Don't forget to bring things I like.

73
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:39,680
I gotta go.

74
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:40,600
Well, Yunhe,

75
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:42,560
let me host a feast for you

76
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:43,600
and ensure your safety.

77
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,160
Safety, my foot.

78
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:45,720
I've got to hurry home

79
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:46,720
for dinner right now.

80
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:47,560
Bye.

81
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:51,720
Prefect,

82
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,520
how dare you arrest my sworn brother?

83
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:54,640
Wait.

84
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:58,040
Who's your sworn brother?

85
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:00,040
I didn't know you actually had

86
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:01,080
a sibling.

87
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:03,640
Li Yunhe is my sworn brother.

88
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:05,160
Oh, Li Yunhe, huh?

89
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:07,160
Didn't you just see him?

90
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:08,280
No one gave him a hard time.

91
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,840
He left on his own.

92
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:12,400
How surprising.

93
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,840
After that brothel scandal,
he still made it back to the Zhous.

94
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:16,680
And now, even after a murder,

95
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:18,120
he walks away unscathed.

96
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,080
That's my brother.

97
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:21,840
Right, that's so incredible.

98
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:24,840
Makes me want
to swear brotherhood with him too.

99
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:26,640
Wait, brother!

100
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:27,600
Brother!

101
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:28,520
Brother!

102
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:35,520
Hey, what did Mr. Lu say?

103
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:38,480
He said

104
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:40,240
we botched the job,

105
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,200
so no pay.

106
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,640
What? Screw him!

107
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:43,600
As the saying goes,

108
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:45,080
even the sovereign
pays his hungry soldiers.

109
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,360
But the Marquis House?

110
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:46,960
They were stingy to begin with,

111
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,320
and that was bad enough,

112
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:49,280
but now they've even stopped

113
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:50,280
paying our monthly wages?

114
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:50,640
Whoever wants

115
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:51,960
this job can have it.

116
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:52,640
Exactly.

117
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:53,560
We quit!

118
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:54,360
That's enough.

119
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:56,160
Keep your voices down.

120
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:58,120
Beware of eavesdroppers.

121
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,360
Understood.

122
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:17,840
It was the Marquis House's men

123
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:19,320
who killed Xue Bingxiu?

124
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:20,720
Yes.

125
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:22,040
It's still unclear

126
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,400
whether they assassinated Xue Bingxiu

127
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,960
to frame Li Yunhe,

128
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:26,680
or if the Marquis House

129
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,560
is colluding with Prince Ning's faction.

130
00:04:29,280 --> 00:04:30,080
Have our men watch them closely.

131
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,840
I suspect the Marquis House

132
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:34,160
has something to hide.

133
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:36,040
Understood.

134
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:43,580
(Zhou Manor)

135
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:58,000
My lady, Mrs. Zhou has returned.

136
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:02,040
Got it.

137
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:11,240
Greetings,

138
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:12,960
Mother.

139
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:15,040
Spare me, Zhou Xingyu.

140
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:17,080
I'm hardly worthy of being your mother.

141
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:18,440
Taking in a live-in husband
is such a monumental decision,

142
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:19,720
and you did it without a word to me,

143
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:21,040
making the decision all on your own.

144
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:22,560
Seems like you're the mother here.

145
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:28,040
Come on, Mother.

146
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,040
Oh, enough.

147
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:30,280
Stop shaking me.

148
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:31,240
Sit properly.

149
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:33,240
I know I was wrong.

150
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,520
That won't happen again.

151
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:35,640
Again? Just how many

152
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:37,080
live-in husbands do you plan to take?

153
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:43,960
Alright now.

154
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:44,840
I know

155
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:46,000
you didn't want to become a concubine

156
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,160
for the Marquis's heir.

157
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:48,240
But you couldn't just...

158
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,440
Look at the mess now.

159
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:51,640
We've completely offended
the Marquis House,

160
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:52,400
and that live-in husband of yours

161
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:54,200
has been thrown in jail for some crime.

162
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:57,000
Just what kind of mess

163
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,640
have you gotten yourself into?

164
00:05:59,160 --> 00:05:59,840
Mother,

165
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:01,720
you've misjudged Li Yunhe.

166
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:03,040
He definitely didn't kill anyone.

167
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:04,040
I believe in him completely.

168
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:04,920
You believe in him completely?

169
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:05,840
On what grounds do you believe him?

170
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:06,440
I...

171
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:08,920
Oh,

172
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,440
let's not talk about this for now.

173
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:11,560
Oh, right,

174
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,240
regarding our family

175
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:14,080
losing the imperial tribute status,

176
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,280
what did you find out?

177
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:16,040
I asked around.

178
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:18,120
It was His Majesty
who personally gave the order

179
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:18,480
to revoke

180
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,800
the Rustling Silk's tribute status.

181
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:22,000
What?

182
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:22,560
Then

183
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:25,120
is there still any hope for us?

184
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:26,560
Don't even think about it.

185
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:28,240
The Weaving Bureau said

186
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,480
that regarding the Rustling Silk affair,

187
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:30,640
our family not being exiled

188
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,120
is already a tremendous act
of imperial mercy.

189
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:35,840
My lady.

190
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:38,080
My lady,

191
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,480
there's a young man
and a young lady outside

192
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,680
who said they wish to see you.

193
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,560
Mr. Zhao, Miss Zhao,

194
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:56,480
have you found

195
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:57,960
a way to save Li Yunhe?

196
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,240
Zhou Xingyu,

197
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:01,640
Li Yunhe said
you've already divorced him.

198
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:03,440
Why do you care so much

199
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:05,040
about a cast-off?

200
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:05,800
I...

201
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:06,880
Miss Zhou,

202
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:09,240
saving Li Yunhe is not difficult.

203
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:10,520
However...

204
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:11,320
What do you mean?

205
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:12,280
However,

206
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:13,200
between saving Li Yunhe

207
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,640
and getting Gambiered Silk

208
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,320
back onto the imperial tribute list,

209
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:17,840
you can only choose one.

210
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:19,560
Choose one?

211
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:21,560
You only get one chance.

212
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:23,960
Think clearly before you answer.

213
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:47,880
What's all the commotion?

214
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:50,640
Were you all waiting for me?

215
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,240
Li Yunhe!

216
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:57,680
You got out!

217
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,440
Did the Prefect give you any trouble?

218
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:00,440
Are you hurt?

219
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:01,400
No.

220
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,000
See?

221
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,440
Good as new, right?

222
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:04,560
Mr. Li,

223
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:06,520
don't tell me you broke out of prison.

224
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:09,280
That's ridiculous, Chunxiang.

225
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:10,520
Don't spout such nonsense ever again.

226
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:11,440
I'm

227
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:13,040
a law-abiding citizen.

228
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:13,720
How could I possibly do something

229
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:14,880
like break out of prison?

230
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:16,400
If you didn't break out,

231
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,440
how did you get out?

232
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:18,320
Did you just fly out?

233
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:19,480
Humph.

234
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:22,440
(Go tell the Prefect)

235
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:23,640
(I can save Xue Bingxiu.)

236
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,040
(Constable Xing,)

237
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:26,400
(take me back)

238
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:27,480
(to Miss Xue's room right now)

239
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,120
(before it's too late.)

240
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:30,240
(Mr. Li,)

241
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:32,440
(you're asking me to release a suspect)

242
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,640
(with everyone watching us?)

243
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:35,120
(Besides,)

244
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:38,040
(the Marquis's heir
is right downstairs.)

245
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:39,760
(The Marquis's heir?)

246
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:41,840
(Constable Xing,)

247
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,720
(do you trust me?)

248
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:46,880
(There's something fishy
about this whole thing.)

249
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:47,960
(We were tipped off)

250
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:49,080
(in advance.)

251
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:55,640
(Alright.)

252
00:08:58,760 --> 00:08:59,560
(Let's go.)

253
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:03,040
Yunhe, thank goodness you were there.

254
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:04,560
If you hadn't spoken up,

255
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:05,640
I might have forgotten.

256
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:07,640
Hand over the deed.

257
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:08,440
The one for Xianquan Tavern.

258
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,720
I'll be taking that.

259
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,000
Haha.

260
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,720
What a lovely surprise.

261
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:20,960
With a few poems

262
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,920
and saving Miss Xue,

263
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,400
I've scored Xianquan Tavern,

264
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:25,480
which is such a massive property.

265
00:09:25,760 --> 00:09:26,840
From here on out,

266
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:29,040
once I shake off this title
of the Zhou live-in son-in-law,

267
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:31,120
I can finally count myself

268
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:33,720
as a man of considerable means
here in Daqian.

269
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:35,120
Are you saying

270
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:36,080
that you won't

271
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,600
be returning to the Zhou Manor?

272
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:38,720
Of course not.

273
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,040
(Zhou Manor)
How can a true man

274
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,720
(Zhou Manor)
who stands between heaven and earth

275
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,120
forever live under someone else's roof?

276
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,240
What's more,

277
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:45,360
I'm now

278
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:47,040
a man of wealth and status.

279
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:48,200
In the future,

280
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:48,680
I won't need

281
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:50,120
to put up with any more dirty looks
from the Zhous.

282
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:54,240
I have things to do.

283
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:55,160
I'll take my leave.

284
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:55,440
Huh?

285
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:56,360
Hey.

286
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:58,080
- Wait, Yu.
- Please know your place, Mr. Li.

287
00:09:58,840 --> 00:09:59,320
I...

288
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,960
Know my place? About what?

289
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:02,440
Yu,

290
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,280
I only said I'm leaving the Zhou Manor.

291
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:05,640
I never said I'd leave you.

292
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:07,640
Yunhe,

293
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:10,080
a real man never lacks for a wife.

294
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:12,360
You just helped the Prefect
stabilize grain prices,

295
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:13,480
and at Chunfeng Pavilion,

296
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:15,160
you swept the poetry competition.

297
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:15,840
By now,

298
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:17,360
you've earned yourself
a fair bit of fame

299
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:18,440
and a tidy fortune.

300
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:19,760
You've already done so much

301
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:20,680
for the Zhou family.

302
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:21,600
Why endure

303
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,520
living at their mercy?

304
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:25,680
Exactly. In my opinion,

305
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:26,840
she's just a blind, greedy fool

306
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:29,120
who doesn't know a good thing
when she sees it.

307
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:30,040
I believe

308
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:31,600
she's completely beneath you.

309
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,240
(Just leave!)

310
00:10:38,880 --> 00:10:39,680
(Wait.)

311
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:43,840
(What are you doing here?)

312
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:44,520
(Go back, now.)

313
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:45,120
(Let go of me!)

314
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:46,040
(Let him go.)

315
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:47,680
(All of you, leave us.)

316
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:48,840
(That's wonderful.)

317
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,240
(Li Yunhe won't have to die.)

318
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:53,240
(My lady!)

319
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:53,920
(- Yu!
- My lady!)

320
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:58,240
Right.

321
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:00,840
A real man never lacks for a wife.

322
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:03,040
But some people

323
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,520
are not meant to be failed.

324
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:08,440
(Zhou Manor)
Yu!

325
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:09,440
(Zhou Manor)
Yu!

326
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,000
Open the gate!

327
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:13,520
I know you're in there.

328
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:15,840
Open up!

329
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:17,680
Let me in!

330
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:20,160
(Zhou Manor)
Huh?

331
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:21,960
Hey,

332
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:23,960
it's me, Li Yunhe.

333
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:25,200
I see.

334
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,240
So you're the live-in son-in-law

335
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:27,760
who slept in a brothel

336
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,560
on his wedding night.

337
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:30,640
Get lost!

338
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:32,920
Weren't you already divorced?

339
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:34,360
What are you doing at the Zhou Manor?

340
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:36,160
What are you talking about?

341
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:37,920
This is my own home.

342
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:38,800
I'm just

343
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:39,960
coming back home.

344
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,040
Li Yunhe,

345
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:44,840
the lady of the house has returned.

346
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:46,040
Your marriage contract
with the Zhou family

347
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:47,040
is null and void.

348
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:48,640
I know it's void.

349
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:50,280
I came to the Zhou Manor

350
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:51,640
not to see you.

351
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:52,840
Stop flattering yourself.

352
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:53,960
I want to see Yu.

353
00:11:54,160 --> 00:11:55,200
You helped

354
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,760
the Feng City Prefect with his strategy

355
00:11:57,760 --> 00:11:59,040
to calm the people

356
00:11:59,080 --> 00:12:00,760
and took first place

357
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:02,320
at the poetry gathering,

358
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:03,560
stealing the spotlight.

359
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:04,640
You're now

360
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:06,840
a well-known, promising young talent.

361
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:08,680
Why must you insist

362
00:12:08,680 --> 00:12:10,360
on living under the Zhou family's eaves?

363
00:12:10,680 --> 00:12:11,920
I'm not here to argue with you.

364
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:12,960
I want to see Yu.

365
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:13,400
I want to see Yu!

366
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:13,960
Guys,

367
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:15,080
close the gate.

368
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:15,680
Hey!

369
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:20,160
I...

370
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:21,880
Open this gate now!

371
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,360
Won't open the gate, huh?

372
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,080
Fine!

373
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:26,080
If you don't open this gate today,

374
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:28,360
I'll just stay right here
and never leave!

375
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:05,960
(Zhou Manor)

376
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:07,560
Mr. Lu? What...

377
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:10,240
What are you doing at the Zhou Manor?

378
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,960
I go wherever I please.

379
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:14,360
Is that any of your business?

380
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:15,840
Li Yunhe,

381
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:18,040
our grudge is far from over.

382
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:22,040
I...

383
00:13:26,920 --> 00:13:28,760
What's he doing at the Zhou Manor?

384
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,200
That's unacceptable.

385
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,920
I have to go ask Mrs. Zhou about this.

386
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:32,760
Stop there!

387
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:35,600
Even if the sky were falling,

388
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:36,840
you can't go in.

389
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:38,400
I absolutely

390
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:39,960
must go in.

391
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:40,840
Get out of my way!

392
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:41,600
Move!

393
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:43,360
Stop right there.

394
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:47,160
Mr. Li,

395
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,520
Mrs. Zhou requests your presence.

396
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:59,000
(Zhou Manor)

397
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:04,520
Zhou Xingyu,

398
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,880
what good
is your stubborn resistance now?

399
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:09,600
The Zhous' fortune is destined

400
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:11,640
to be mine for the taking.

401
00:14:12,360 --> 00:14:12,920
My lord,

402
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:16,240
no matter how extraordinary
Zhou Xingyu's spirit is,

403
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:18,360
she's still nothing
but a merchant's daughter.

404
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:19,440
Besides,

405
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:20,560
the Rustling Silk

406
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:21,880
has already lost

407
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:23,560
its imperial tribute status.

408
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:25,080
Soon the Zhous will be reduced

409
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:26,280
to nothing but a stray dog.

410
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:29,720
Why must it be her, and no one else?

411
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:31,520
What do you know?

412
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:34,640
The Feng City Prefect
threw the doors wide open

413
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:36,160
and spread word far and wide.

414
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:38,640
That country bumpkin Li Yunhe

415
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:40,440
used that poetry gathering

416
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:42,840
to peddle the Gambiered Silk.

417
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:45,240
He's piqued enormous interest.

418
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:46,120
Too bad

419
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:48,040
they're only interested

420
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:49,560
in the Zhous' Gambiered Silk.

421
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:50,640
So,

422
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:52,440
to get their money,

423
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:55,160
I must first seize the Zhou household.

424
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:56,640
What's more,

425
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:58,440
the Marquis House's storehouses

426
00:14:58,440 --> 00:14:59,480
are bursting with grain.

427
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:01,360
What we lack is money.

428
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:03,920
And now, the Zhous have
the most liquid silver in all Feng City.

429
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,160
With money,

430
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,040
we can arm our forces

431
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:08,040
and raise our troops.

432
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:09,160
(Grain,)

433
00:15:09,160 --> 00:15:09,800
(arms,)

434
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:10,760
(and troops?)

435
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,600
(What the Marquis House is after)

436
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:15,080
(is nothing less
than the entire realm of Daqian.)

437
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:18,080
My lord, by my calculation,

438
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:19,960
it's been quite some time

439
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,560
since Li Yunhe
married into the Zhou family.

440
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:24,520
I wonder if Ms. Zhou is still...

441
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:26,640
Mrs. Zhou has already made it

442
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:27,720
quite clear to me.

443
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:29,320
The Zhou heiress

444
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:31,440
is still pure and untouched.

445
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:33,720
After this very night,

446
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:36,640
Li Yunhe will be thrown out
of the Zhou household for good.

447
00:15:36,960 --> 00:15:38,040
When that time comes...

448
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:40,760
I have

449
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:42,440
a thousand ways

450
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:43,640
to make that nobody

451
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:45,240
disappear from the face of this earth.

452
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,720
Greetings, my mother-in-law.

453
00:16:04,320 --> 00:16:05,360
I mean, Mrs. Zhou.

454
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:09,320
Greetings, Mrs. Zhou.

455
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:10,320
Hold it right there.

456
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:12,440
I'll ask you a few questions.

457
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:13,360
Once you answer them,

458
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:13,840
then we can talk

459
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,520
about titles and etiquette.
There's no rush.

460
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:17,720
If you don't want to give me Yu's hand,

461
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:19,040
you can just say so outright.

462
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:20,360
No need to toy with me like this.

463
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:21,840
How dare you!

464
00:16:51,580 --> 00:16:55,180
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

465
00:16:55,340 --> 00:16:58,540
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

466
00:16:59,060 --> 00:17:01,780
♪Who took the March rain♪

467
00:17:02,020 --> 00:17:05,380
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

468
00:17:05,740 --> 00:17:08,540
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

469
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:11,900
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

470
00:17:12,780 --> 00:17:18,700
♪Needle and thread
stitch away the marks of time♪

471
00:17:18,740 --> 00:17:22,180
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

472
00:17:22,420 --> 00:17:25,260
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

473
00:17:25,420 --> 00:17:27,700
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

474
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:31,900
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

475
00:17:31,980 --> 00:17:35,260
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

476
00:17:35,420 --> 00:17:38,540
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

477
00:17:39,060 --> 00:17:41,980
♪In this life I'd be a cloud-tailor♪

478
00:17:42,140 --> 00:17:48,660
♪Never failing the stars,
nor failing you♪

479
00:18:14,940 --> 00:18:18,460
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

480
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:21,860
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

481
00:18:22,460 --> 00:18:25,180
♪Who took the March rain♪

482
00:18:25,380 --> 00:18:28,700
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

483
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:31,980
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

484
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:35,780
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

485
00:18:35,820 --> 00:18:39,100
♪Warp and weft entwine,
one shuttle, one dream♪

486
00:18:39,100 --> 00:18:42,060
♪As seasons change♪

487
00:18:42,060 --> 00:18:45,700
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

488
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:48,540
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

489
00:18:48,620 --> 00:18:51,180
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

490
00:18:51,180 --> 00:18:55,260
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

491
00:18:55,260 --> 00:18:58,580
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

492
00:18:58,580 --> 00:19:02,300
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

493
00:19:02,700 --> 00:19:05,820
♪Washing away
a lifetime of wear and tear♪

494
00:19:05,820 --> 00:19:08,700
♪Only for you♪

495
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:12,300
♪On the street of golden honors,
the music rises♪

496
00:19:12,420 --> 00:19:15,180
♪The moon moves west
beyond the pavilion♪

497
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:17,860
♪Wine runs dry, yet the revelry lingers♪

498
00:19:17,860 --> 00:19:21,940
♪In silk, I seek a kindred soul♪

499
00:19:21,940 --> 00:19:25,260
♪The rain has ceased,
clouds begin to clear♪

500
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:28,660
♪The fragrant silk billows
under the low-hung stars♪

501
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:35,180
♪I'd cut the clouds and morning glow
to drape over you♪

502
00:19:36,260 --> 00:19:40,380
♪A single bolt of silk becomes♪

503
00:19:41,660 --> 00:19:46,180
♪Your wedding gown♪
